column1: Will ACLED record any civilian fatalities in Tunisia between 15 October 2017 and 31 October 2017?
column6: ['Security and Conflict']
column11: The Armed Conflict Location and Event Dataset (ACLED) summarizes press reports on conflict and protest events in Africa and parts of Asia. Outcome will be determined by the "Realtime [Month of Interest] All Africa File" found on the Realtime Data page (ACLED). The question will resolve as "yes" if ACLED records any event for which: 'COUNTRY' is the country of interest; 'EVENT_DATE' falls in the period of interest; and 'EVENT_TYPE' is Violence against civilians, or Remote violence; and 'FATALITIES' is greater than or equal to 1. Question will be resolved when the relevant data is first released. If a qualifying event is recorded, the question will be closed retroactively with the date of the first event as the end date of the question. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

He last event of violence against civilians/remote violence in Tunisia occurred on August 19 and 25. No events of this particular type has occurred any time after that. There is always the possibility of an event or events of this nature occurring between today and the end of October. However, the conditional probability of this event is: .01 < Event < .50. The conditional probability of event type of protests has a larger value, therefore, P(Protests | violence against civilians ) > .50
